name: java
description: Java is a general-purpose programming language that is class-based, object-oriented, and designed to have as few implementation dependencies as possible. It is intended to let application developers write once, run anywhere (WORA).

name: Database design
description: Database design is the organization of data according to a logical structure of a database. So the goal is to determine in which manner data can be stored, organized and manipulated. Database design involves classifying data and identifying relationships.

name: algorithms
description: In mathematics and computer science, an algorithm is a finite sequence of well-defined instructions, typically to solve a class of problems such as doing some calculations, data processing, automated reasoning, and other tasks.

name: data structures
description: A data structure is a data organization, management, and storage format that enables efficient access and modification. More precisely, a DS is a collection of data values, the relationships among them, and the operations that can be applied to the data.

name: programming
description: Programming is the process of creating a set of instructions that tell a computer how to perform a task. Programming can be done using a variety of computer programming languages, such as JavaScript, Python, and C++.

name: javascript
description: JavaScript (JS) is a lightweight, interpreted, or just-in-time compiled programming language with first-class functions. While it is most well-known as the scripting language for Web pages, many non-browser environments also use it, such as Node.js.
